<h2>7.4 Privacy Protection (AIR-SHIELD)</h2>

<p>Zero-knowledge verification for sensitive scenarios:</p>

<h3>Selective Disclosure</h3>

<pre>
Scenario: Employer wants to verify "has medical degree"
Without revealing: specific university, grades, dates

Zero-Knowledge Proof Request:
{
  "claim": "has_credential_type",
  "credentialType": "medical_degree",
  "level": "doctorate",
  "minConfidence": 70
}

ZK Proof Response:
{
  "proofValid": true,
  "claim": "has_credential_type",
  "confidence": 78,
  "proof": "zk:...",  // Cryptographic proof
  "revealed": {
    "credentialType": "medical_degree",
    "level": "doctorate"
  },
  "hidden": [
    "institution",
    "graduation_date",
    "gpa"
  ]
}
</pre>

